  "texts": [
    "The TURN method adopts the brand-new temporal action proposal (TAP) indicator AR-F to solve the above two problems.",
    "However, it does not fundamentally solve the problem of inaccurate division of the action boundary.",
    "Because most current models obtain good results through predetermined anchor points, they are susceptible to the interference of a large number of outputs and different anchor sizes.",
    "Lin et al. (2021) proposed a completely anchor-free temporal positioning method in 2021, which is more portable.",
    "The overall framework is divided into three parts:"
  ]
